# Full System Upgrade Plan

Three features combined into one implementation:
1. **Registration + Approval** — step-by-step student onboarding, bookings start as `pending`
2. **Waitlist** — if a group is full, student joins a queue and is notified when a spot opens
3. **General Interest** — if no group time works, student leaves a preferred time note

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Pending bookings and capacity:** A pending booking **does not** reserve a seat. A seat is only locked when the teacher approves. This prevents unreviewed requests from blocking real students. Confirm this is intended.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Waitlist notifications are push-only.** When a spot opens, the bot messages all waitlisted students automatically. There is no manual "offer" step — all waitlisted students for that group get notified simultaneously and whoever books first wins the seat.

---

## Database Migrations

Run this SQL on Supabase **before** deploying:

```sql
-- 1. Add fields to students
ALTER TABLE students
  ADD COLUMN phone_number TEXT,
  ADD COLUMN is_registered BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE;

-- 2. Add status + parent_phone to bookings
CREATE TYPE booking_status AS ENUM ('pending', 'approved', 'rejected');
ALTER TABLE bookings
  ADD COLUMN status        booking_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
  ADD COLUMN parent_phone  TEXT;

-- 3. New waitlist_requests table
CREATE TYPE waitlist_type AS ENUM ('waitlist', 'general');

CREATE TABLE waitlist_requests (
  id                  UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  student_id          UUID        NOT NULL REFERENCES students(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  group_id            UUID        REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  preferred_time_text TEXT,
  type                waitlist_type NOT NULL,
  notified_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Index for fast lookup when a spot opens
CREATE INDEX idx_waitlist_group ON waitlist_requests (group_id) WHERE type = 'waitlist';
-- Index for notifying general interest users when new group is added
CREATE INDEX idx_waitlist_general ON waitlist_requests (type) WHERE type = 'general';
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Capacity trigger update:** The existing `trg_manage_booking_count` trigger increments `booked_count` on INSERT. Since pending bookings should not consume capacity, the trigger must be updated to only increment when `status = 'approved'`. The API's `PATCH /bookings/:id/status` will handle the increment on approval instead.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend API

#### [MODIFY] [students.js](file:///d:/DIV%20WORK/Coding/%D8%AD%D8%AC%D8%B2/src/routes/students.js)
- `POST /students` — add `phone_number`, `is_registered` fields
- `GET /students/:telegram_user_id` — no change

#### [MODIFY] [bookings.js](file:///d:/DIV%20WORK/Coding/%D8%AD%D8%AC%D8%B2/src/routes/bookings.js)
- `POST /bookings` — add `parent_phone`, insert with `status = 'pending'`, **no capacity decrement**
- `GET /bookings?student_id=` — return `status`, `group_name`, `grade_name`
- **[NEW]** `PATCH /bookings/:id/status` — `{ status: 'approved' | 'rejected' }`. On `approved`: increment `booked_count`, notify student. On `rejected`: notify student.
- **[NEW]** `GET /bookings/pending` — all pending bookings with student + group info (admin use)

#### [NEW] [waitlist.js](file:///d:/DIV%20WORK/Coding/%D8%AD%D8%AC%D8%B2/src/routes/waitlist.js)
- `POST /waitlist` — `{ student_id, group_id?, preferred_time_text?, type }` — insert a waitlist or general interest record
- `GET /waitlist?group_id=` — get all waitlist entries for a group (used to notify on approval cancellation)
- `GET /waitlist/general` — get all general interest entries (used to notify on new group)

